## Algorithm 1 HST-Conformal

Require: Dataset $\mathcal{D}$, network topology $\mathbf{C}$, significance level $\alpha$, sample size $K$, prediction model $\lambda_{t}^{*}$.
Initialize $\mathcal{E}_{i}=\emptyset$ for all $i=1, \ldots, n$.
Split $\mathcal{D}$ into training set $\mathcal{D}_{\mathrm{tr}}$ and calibration set $\mathcal{D}_{\mathrm{cal}}$;
Fit model $\widehat{\lambda}_{t}^{*}$ on $\mathcal{D}_{\mathrm{tr}}$ by maximizing the likelihood;
for $t \in\left\{t_{0}, \ldots, T\right\}$ do
Simulate $K$ outcomes $\widehat{y}_{t}^{(1)}, \ldots, \widehat{y}_{t}^{(K)} \sim \widehat{\lambda}_{t}^{*}$;
for $i \in\{1, \ldots, n\}$ do
Compute $\widehat{e}_{i t}$ using (2);
$\mathcal{E}_{i} \leftarrow \mathcal{E}_{i} \cup\left\{\widehat{e}_{i t}\right\}$
end for
end for
Compute $\alpha$-empirical quantile $\widehat{q}_{i}(\alpha)$ from $\mathcal{E}_{i}$ for each $i$;
Simulate $K$ outcomes $\widehat{y}_{T+1}^{(1)}, \ldots, \widehat{y}_{T+1}^{(K)} \sim \widehat{\lambda}_{T+1}^{*}$;
Output prediction intervals according to (3).
